/*------------------Level 1------------------*/

@1=~Bless~
@2=~Bless
Level: 1
School: Enchantment
Sphere: All
Range: Long
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 30' radius
Saving Throw: None

Upon uttering the Bless spell, the priest grants a +1 bonus to THAC0, damage, and morale to friendly creatures. The caster determines at what range they will cast the spell, and the instant the spell is completed, it affects all creatures in a 30 foot radius centered on the point selected by the caster. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative.~

@3=~Command~
@4=~Command
Level: 1
School: Enchantment
Sphere: Charm, Combat, Law
Range: Long
Duration: 1 round
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Spell negates

This spell enables the priest to command another creature to lie down and take no action (sleep) for a single round. The target has a saving throw penalty of -1 for every two extra experience levels of the caster, up to a maximum of -4 at 9th level.~ //Elves and half-elves are particularly resistant to sleep effects, while the undead and certain other creatures such as constructs, dragons, elementals, and illusions are completely immune to magically-induced sleep.

@5=~Cure Light Wounds~
@6=~Cure Light Wounds
Level: 1
School: Necromancy
Sphere: Healing
Range: Touch
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When casting this spell and laying their hand upon a creature, the priest heals the wounds and injuries of the target. The priest can restore 10 + 1/two levels hit points, up to a maximum of 20 at 20th level.~ //This healing cannot affect creatures of incorporeal or extraplanar origin.~

@7=~Detect Alignment~
@8=~Detect Alignment
Level: 1
School: Divination
Sphere: Divination
Range: Personal
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This spell allows the priest to search out the feelings of all creatures within the current area. When affected by this spell, a target will briefly glow red if they're evil, green if they're good, and white if they're neutral. Magic resistance does not affect this spell.~

@9=~Entangle~
@10=~Entangle
Level: 1
School: Alteration
Sphere: Plant
Range: Long
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 30' radius
Saving Throw: Breath partial

By means of this spell, the caster causes plants to spring up from the ground and entangle all creatures in the area of effect. The grasses, weeds, bushes, and even trees wrap, twist, and entwine about creatures in the area, holding them fast for the duration of the spell. Those held receive a -2 penalty to THAC0 and AC. Creatures that make a save vs. breath temporarily avoid entanglement and can move at half their normal movement rate through the area, but must make an additional saving throw each round that they remain in the area of effect. An entangled creature can attack, provided it does not have to move to reach an opponent. Incorporeal and flying creatures are unaffected by this spell, as are elementals and exceptionally large and strong creatures who suffer little to no distress from the entangling plants.~

@11=~Magical Stone~
@12=~Magical Stone
Level: 1
School: Enchantment
Sphere: Combat
Range: Personal
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

Using this spell, the priest can temporarily enchant ten small stones, no larger than sling bullets. When thrown, each stone deals 1D4 + 2 missile damage (1D4 + 5 against undead) upon a successful hit, and the caster can hurl up to three stones per round. The caster wields them as if proficient and at their normal base THAC0, and they are considered to be of +1 enchantment (with appropriate THAC0 and damage bonuses) to determine what they can hit. The stones can be used only by the caster, and remain in their hand for 5 turns or until used.~

@13=~Protection from Evil~
@14=~Protection from Evil
Level: 1
School: Abjuration
Sphere: Protection
Range: Touch
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast, it creates a magical barrier around the recipient at a distance of one foot. The barrier moves with the recipient and has two major effects: first, all attacks made by evil creatures against the protected creature receive a -2 penalty to their THAC0, and second, any saving throws caused by such attacks are made by the protected creature with a +2 bonus. Multiple castings of this spell or similar effects are not cumulative.~

@15=~Resist Fear~
@16=~Resist Fear
Level: 1
School: Abjuration
Sphere: Charm
Range: Long
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 30' radius
Saving Throw: None

The priest instills courage in allies, raising their morale to its highest. If the recipients are affected by magical fear, this is negated, and they are protected from it for the duration of the spell. The instant the spell is completed, it affects all creatures in a 30 foot radius centered on the point selected by the caster.~

@17=~Sanctuary~
@18=~Sanctuary
Level: 1
School: Abjuration
Sphere: Charm, Protection
Range: Personal
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

When the priest casts a Sanctuary spell, it causes all opponents to ignore their existence, as if they were invisible. While protected by this spell, the priest cannot take direct offensive action without breaking the spell, but may use non-attack spells focused on themselves or otherwise act in any way that does not violate the prohibition against offensive action. This allows a warded priest to heal their wounds, for example, or to cast a Chant spell, but they cannot cast spells on other targets without ending the spell.~

@19=~Shillelagh~
@20=~Shillelagh
Level: 1
School: Alteration
Sphere: Combat, Plant
Range: Personal
Duration: 1 turn + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This spell enables the caster to create a magical cudgel. Dealing 2D4 + 1 crushing damage upon a successful hit, this shillelagh also causes tendrils to wrap around and hold the victim in place for 1 round unless they successfully make a save vs. breath. The caster wields the shillelagh as if proficient and at their normal base THAC0, and it is considered to be of +1 enchantment (with appropriate THAC0 and damage bonuses) to determine what it can hit. This enchantment level increases by one for every four extra experience levels of the caster, up to a maximum of +3 at 9th level. Strength modifiers do not apply to THAC0 or damage, and attacks with the shillelagh are considered to be melee touch attacks (+4 bonus to THAC0). The shillelagh can be used only by the caster, and remains in their hand for the duration of the spell.~

@21=~Armor of Faith~
@22=~Armor of Faith
Level: 1
School: Abjuration
Sphere: Protection
Range: Personal
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

The caster of the Armor of Faith spell receives significant protection against physical and magic damage. This magical armor is a force of energy that absorbs a portion of the damage intended for the caster, effectively reducing damage sustained by 10%. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative.~

@23=~Doom~
@24=~Doom
Level: 1
School: Enchantment
Sphere: Charm
Range: Long
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Spell negates

This spell causes a feeling of doom to overwhelm the target. For the duration of the spell, the target suffers a -2 penalty to THAC0, damage, and saving throws. The creature may make a save vs. spell at a penalty of -1 for every two extra experience levels of the caster, up to a maximum of -4 at 9th level. Multiple castings of this spell or similar effects are not cumulative.~

@25=~Faerie Fire~
@26=~Faerie Fire
Level: 1
School: Evocation
Sphere: Weather
Range: Long
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 20' radius
Saving Throw: Special

When this spell is cast, a pale glow surrounds and outlines all enemies within the area of effect, making their position and movements easily visible. Invisible creatures are revealed, and those who do not successfully make a saving throw vs. spell are distinctly outlined for the next 5 rounds. Outlined creatures do not benefit from the concealment normally provided by stealth, invisibility, or similar effects, and suffer a -2 penalty to AC. The faerie fire light is too dim to have any special effect on undead or dark-dwelling creatures vulnerable to light, and does not cause any harm to the objects or creatures thus outlined. Multiple castings of this spell or similar effects are not cumulative.~

@27=~Strength of Stone~
@28=~Strength of Stone
Level: 1
School: Alteration
Sphere: Elemental (Earth)
Range: Personal
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

Calling upon the strength of the earth, the caster gains some of the solidity and strength of stone, setting their strength to 18 and adding an additional +50 exceptional strength on top of this, and they receive any Strength bonuses appropriate. For example, if a character has between 18/50 and 18/00 Strength, then their Strength will just be set to 18/00, while if a character has a Strength between 18/01 and 18/50, then their Strength will become 18/50 + the original percentage. If their Strength is less then 18, then it will just become 18/50. However, this spell will actually lower a character's Strength if it is already 19 or more. For the duration of the spell, the caster also becomes immune to everything, magical or otherwise, that pushes them away, such as wing buffets, telekinesis, Gust of Wind, and Battering Ram.~

@29=~Sunscorch~
@30=~Sunscorch
Level: 1
School: Evocation
Sphere: Sun
Range: Long
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Breath partial

When this spell is cast, a brilliant ray of scorching heat slants down from the sky and strikes a creature chosen by the caster. The target struck by the ray is blinded for 1 round and suffers 1D6 + 1/level fire damage, up to a maximum of 1D6 + 10 at 10th level. The target may make a save vs. breath to avoid being blinded and receive only half damage. Undead creatures and other monsters vulnerable to bright light suffer double damage and double length blindness. Magic resistance does not affect this spell.~

@301=~Regenerate Light Wounds~
@302=~Regenerate Light Wounds
Level: 1
School: Alteration
Sphere: Healing
Range: Touch
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This spell enables the caster to mend the wounds and injuries of the target by granting them temporary regeneration. The affected creature will regenerate 15 + 1.5/two levels hit points over the duration of the spell, up to a maximum of 30 at 20th level.~

@44000=~Goodberry
Level: 1
School: Alteration
Sphere: Plant
Range: Personal
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

Casting a Goodberry spell creates 3 magical berries that the caster can carry with them or give to others. When consumed, these berries restore 5 hit points and one additional hit point for every three experience levels of the caster, up to a maximum of 10 at 15th level. The berries last for 24 hours or until eaten.~

@315=~Cause Light Wounds~
@316=~Cause Light Wounds
Level: 1
School: Necromancy
Sphere: Necromantic
Range: Personal
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This spell is the reverse of Cure Light Wounds. Instead of healing the creature touched, it causes injuries. On a successful touch from the priest, the target suffers 1D10 + 1/level magic damage, up to a maximum of 1D10 + 10 at 10th level. The spell expires once the priest makes a successful melee touch attack (+4 bonus to THAC0) or after 1 turn has passed. Magic resistance does not affect this spell.~

@319=~Animal Summoning I~
@320=~Animal Summoning I
Level: 1
School: Conjuration
Sphere: Animal
Range: Long
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

By means of this spell, the caster calls a number of animals that serve the summoner. The type and number of creatures that appear depend upon the level of the druid casting the spell. The summoned animals will aid the caster under any condition and by whatever means they possess, staying until the spell duration expires.

1st: 3 bats
3rd: 4 bats
5th: 5 bats

Bat (1 HD):
 ST9, DE14, CO11, IN4, WI11, CH4
 HP 4, AC 8, THAC0 20, APR 1
 1D2 Piercing (Bite)
 Saving Throws 13/17/15/13/17, AL TN
 SR 0%, CR 0%, PR 0%, MR 0%
 FR 0%, CR 0%, ER 0%, AR 0%

Special Characteristics:
 Blind Sense: relies on echolocation to fight in conditions of poor light or total darkness, ignoring the penalties associated with blindness
 Diseasing: target suffers a -1 penalty to Dexterity and Constitution for 8 hours (save vs. death neg.)
 Swarm: each bat within 10' receives a +2 bonus to THAC0~

@321=~Obscuring Mist~
@322=~Obscuring Mist
Level: 1
School: Conjuration
Sphere: Weather
Range: Long
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 20' radius
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast, a misty bank of fog billows out from the designated point, obscuring all sight. Everyone within the cloud suffers a -2 penalty to THAC0 while their visibility range is reduced by half, and anyone inside or outside the cloud trying to attack a creature concealed by the fog with ranged weapons will do so with a -4 penalty to THAC0. Creatures that do not rely on sight can fight within the cloud without penalties.~


/*------------------Level 2------------------*/

@31=~Aid~
@32=~Aid
Level: 2
School: Necromancy
Sphere: Combat, Necromantic
Range: Touch
Duration: 1 turn/level
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

The recipient of this spell gains a +1 bonus to THAC0, damage, and saving throws. They also gain 1D8 + 1/level temporary hit points, up to a maximum of 1D8 + 10 at 10th level. This spell allows the recipient to temporarily have more hit points than their full normal total, and these bonus hit points are lost first when the recipient takes damage. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative.~

@33=~Barkskin~
@34=~Barkskin
Level: 2
School: Alteration
Sphere: Plant
Range: Touch
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When a druid casts the Barkskin spell upon a creature, their skin becomes as tough as bark, giving them a +2 bonus to AC that increases by 1 for every six extra experience levels of the caster, up to a maximum of +4 at 15th level. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative.~

@35=~Chant~
@36=~Chant
Level: 2
School: Conjuration
Sphere: Combat
Range: Personal
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: 30' radius
Saving Throw: None

By means of the Chant spell, the priest brings special favor upon themselves and their party while causing harm to their enemies. When the chant is completed, the THAC0, damage, and saving throws of those in the area of effect who are friendly to the priest gain a +1 bonus, while those hostile to the priest suffer a -1 penalty. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative.~

@37=~Charm Person or Animal~
@38=~Charm Person or Animal
Level: 2
School: Enchantment
Sphere: Animal
Range: Long
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 person or animal
Saving Throw: Spell negates

This spell affects any single person or animal that it is cast upon. The term "person" includes any bipedal human, demihuman, or humanoid of man-size or smaller, such as dwarves, elves, gnolls, gnomes, half-elves, halflings, half-orcs, hobgoblins, kobolds, and others. Only normal and giant sized animals are affected by this spell. Monsters such as wyverns, ankhegs, and carrion crawlers do not count as animals. If the target fails their save vs. spell, they regard the caster as a trusted friend and ally to be heeded and protected for the duration of the spell. The caster may give them orders, and the charmed creature will carry them out as quickly as possible.

If the caster attempts to harm the charmed creature, or if a dispel magic is successfully cast upon them, the spell is broken. If two or more charm effects simultaneously affect a creature, the most recent charm takes precedence. After the duration of the spell, the affected creature resumes their previous behavior prior to being charmed.~

@39=~Find Traps~
@40=~Find Traps
Level: 2
School: Divination
Sphere: Divination
Range: Personal
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 30' radius
Saving Throw: None

When a priest casts a Find Traps spell, all traps - concealed normally or magically - of magical or mechanical nature become apparent to them. Once per round, all traps within a 30 foot radius of the caster will be revealed. A trap is any device or magical ward that meets three criteria: it can create a sudden or unexpected result, the caster would view the result as undesirable or harmful, and the creator specifically intended the harmful or undesirable result as such. Thus, "traps" include glyphs and similar spells and devices.~

@41=~Flame Blade~
@42=~Flame Blade
Level: 2
School: Evocation
Sphere: Elemental (Fire)
Range: Personal
Duration: 1 turn + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

With this spell, the caster causes a blazing ray of red-hot fire to spring forth from their hand, dealing 2D6 + 1 fire damage upon a successful hit. The caster wields this blade-like ray as if proficient with the weapon and at their normal base THAC0, and it is considered to be of +1 enchantment (with appropriate THAC0 and damage bonuses) to determine what it can hit. This enchantment level increases by one for every three extra experience levels of the caster, up to a maximum of +3 at 9th level. Since the blade is immaterial, Strength modifiers do not apply to THAC0 or damage, and attacks with the flame blade are considered to be melee touch attacks (+4 bonus to THAC0). The flame blade can be used only by the caster, and remains in their hand for the duration of the spell.~

@43=~Goodberry~
@44=~Goodberry
Level: 2
School: Alteration
Sphere: Plant
Range: Personal
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

Casting a Goodberry spell creates 3 magical berries that the caster can carry with them or give to others. When consumed, these berries restore 5 hit points and one additional hit point for every three experience levels of the caster, up to a maximum of 10 at 15th level. The berries last for 24 hours or until eaten.~

@45=~Hold Person~
@46=~Hold Person
Level: 2
School: Enchantment
Sphere: Charm, Law
Range: Long
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: Target, and enemies within 5'
Saving Throw: Spell negates

This spell holds one or more humans, demihumans, or humanoid creatures rigidly immobile and in place for 1 turn. The effect is centered on the target selected by the caster, and every enemy within 5 feet of the target is also affected. Creatures who make a save vs. spell are totally unaffected by the spell. The undead cannot be held with this spell.

Held creatures cannot move or speak, but they remain aware of events around them even though they are helpless to change them. Time passes at a normal rate for the targets and hence being held does not stop any worsening of their condition due to wounds, disease, or poison.~

@47=~Know Opponent~
@48=~Know Opponent
Level: 2
School: Divination
Sphere: Divination
Range: Long
Duration: 1 turn + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When a Know Opponent spell is cast, the priest's eyes glow with magical energy, enabling them to read the aura of the target and determine their strengths and weaknesses. For the duration of the spell, the target's physical resistances are lowered by 10% and all attacks against them are made with a +2 bonus to THAC0. Certain magical devices negate the power of the Know Opponent spell, and the spell has no effect on creatures who don't emanate auras, such as constructs. Magic resistance does not affect this spell, and multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative.~

@49=~Resist Elements~
@50=~Resist Elements
Level: 2
School: Abjuration
Sphere: Protection
Range: Touch
Duration: 1 turn + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

Upon the casting of this spell, the recipient gains a +25% bonus to elemental resistance (fire, cold, electricity, and acid). Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative.~

@51=~Silence~
@52=~Silence
Level: 2
School: Alteration
Sphere: Guardian
Range: Long
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 20' radius
Saving Throw: Spell negates

Upon casting this spell, complete silence prevails in the affected area. All sound is stopped: conversation is impossible and spells cannot be cast unless an affected creature then casts Vocalize. All enemies in the area must make a save vs. spell at a -4 penalty or be silenced for the duration of the spell.~

@53=~Slow Poison~
@54=~Slow Poison
Level: 2
School: Necromancy
Sphere: Healing
Range: Touch
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast upon a poisoned individual, it greatly slows the effects of poisons and vemons, actually neutralizing all but the most deadly of afflictions.~

@55=~Spiritual Hammer~
@56=~Spiritual Hammer
Level: 2
School: Evocation
Sphere: Combat
Range: Personal
Duration: 1 turn + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

By calling upon their deity, the caster of a Spiritual Hammer spell brings into existence a field of force shaped vaguely like a hammer. For as long as the caster concentrates upon the hammer, it can be used to strike at any opponents within 20 feet, dealing 1D8 + 1 magic damage upon a successful hit. The caster wields the spiritual hammer as if proficient and at their normal base THAC0, and it functions as a magical weapon with an enchantment bonus of +1 (with appropriate THAC0 and damage bonuses). Starting at level 5, this enchantment level increases by one for every five extra experience levels of the caster, up to a maximum of +5 at 25th level. Due to its ethereal nature, Strength modifiers do not apply to THAC0 or damage, and attacks with the spiritual weapon are considered to be melee touch attacks (+4 bonus to THAC0). The spiritual hammer can be used only by the caster, and remains in their hand for the duration of the spell.~

@57=~Draw Upon Divine Might~
@58=~Draw Upon Divine Might
Level: 2
School: Evocation
Sphere: Combat
Range: Personal
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast, the priest's body shudders and glows with a shimmering aura as it becomes a vessel for the power of their god. When they do this, they gain a +1 bonus to Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution scores for every three levels of the caster, up to a maximum of +3 at 9th level. Multiple castings of this spell or similar effects are not cumulative.~

@59=~Cure Medium Wounds~
@60=~Cure Medium Wounds
Level: 2
